{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"brownie tin (32 cm x 18 cm), baking paper, skewer, pastry brush, wire rack, oven","id":"r304772","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-o1OcefM0vrQ\/XZWqJkw8cxI\/AAAAAAAAfTw\/yuH1qCD0RycbDQXdbjl3PAqfi8podWRPwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_DmBxn9rwgIl-Ie6Z.png","title":"Plum and Almond Traybake","publishedAt":"2018-12-03T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"content":"60 g blanched almonds"},{"content":"220 g unsalted butter, soft"},{"content":"220 g caster sugar"},{"content":"270 g self-raising flour"},{"content":"3 large eggs"},{"content":"1 tsp vanilla extract"},{"content":"9 plums, halved, stone removed"},{"content":"2 Tbsp flaked almonds"},{"content":"1 Tbsp apricot jam"},{"content":"1 Tbsp water, boiling"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"4 g","fat":"13.4 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"28 g","calories":"1063 kJ \/ 254 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Preheat oven to 180°C and line a brownie tin (32 cm x 18 cm) with baking paper, allowing edges to overhang (see tip)."},{"content":"Place almonds in mixing bowl and grind <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."},{"content":"Place butter and sugar in mixing bowl then cream <b>1 min\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Add flour, eggs, vanilla extract and reserved ground almonds then mix <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then mix again <b>30 sec\/speed 4<b>."},{"content":"Transfer to prepared tin and spread out evenly. Press plum halves, cut side up, into mixture then scatter with flaked almonds. Bake for 40-45 minutes (180°C) until golden and a skewer inserted in sponge comes out clean."},{"content":"Leave to cool in tin for 5 minutes before removing to a wire rack."},{"content":"Dissolve apricot jam in boiling water then brush over surface of cake. Serve warm or cold, on its own or with crème fraîche."}],"hintsAndTricks":["A great way to enjoy sweet English plums, particularly in the autumn months when the fruits are at their ripest. Combined with almonds, it's delicious served warm with crème fraîche as a pudding or cold as a teatime treat. <b>Serving 18,<b> it's also a good choice when there's a crowd to feed!","Use the overhanging baking paper as handles to help remove the traybake from the tin.","Substitute plums with fresh or tinned apricots.","Add <b>1 tsp<b> almond extract in <b>step 4<b> for an even more intense nutty flavour."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 5m","18 pieces"]}